    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Antenatal Care Plan - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_antenatal_care_plan">Antenatal Care Plan</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_plan">CARE PLAN</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_antenatal_care_plan">Antenatal Care Plan</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_plan">CARE PLAN</xref>
 developed within a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_maternity_episode">Maternity Episode</xref>
 for the delivery of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_antenatal">Antenatal</xref>
 care.        </p>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_antenatal_care_plan">Antenatal Care Plan</xref>
 should include details of medical history, the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONALS</xref>
 to be involved and their 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional_role">CARE PROFESSIONAL ROLES</xref>, information about the delivery of each 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>, information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_antenatal">Antenatal</xref>
 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_clinical_investigation">Clinical Investigations</xref>
 and activities.        </p>
  </div>
